 108:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        [..]
 109:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        By default, after the HAL_SPI_Init() and when the state is HAL_SPI_STATE_RESET
 110:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 111:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        examples HAL_SPI_MasterTxCpltCallback(), HAL_SPI_MasterRxCpltCallback().
 112:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 113:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_SPI_Init()/ HAL_SPI_DeInit() only when
 114:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 115:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_SPI_Init()/ HAL_SPI_DeInit()
 116:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state
 117:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 118:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        [..]
 119:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_SPI_STATE_READY state only.
 120:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 121:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        in HAL_SPI_STATE_READY or HAL_SPI_STATE_RESET state,
 122:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 123:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 124:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        using HAL_SPI_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_SPI_DeInit()
 125:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c ****        or HAL_SPI_Init() function.
 126:Drivers/STM32F0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f0xx_hal_spi.c **** 
